# User Registration System

A simple user registration system using HTML for the front-end, Node.js for the back-end, and MongoDB for data storage.


## Overview

This project provides a basic user registration system that allows users to sign up and store their information securely in a MongoDB database. The system includes a registration form created using HTML and styled with CSS. The back-end, built with Node.js, handles form submissions and stores user data in MongoDB.

## Features

- User-friendly registration form.
- Secure storage of user information in MongoDB.
- Express server for handling form submissions.

## Requirements

Make sure you have the following installed on your machine:

- Node.js
- MongoDB

## Installation

 Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/Aryan-Singh1011/user-registration-system.git

Navigate to the project directory:
 cd user-registration-system

Install dependencies:
 npm install

Start the server:
 node app.js


Usage:-
 Access the registration form in your browser at http://localhost:3000.
 Fill out the form with a username, email, and password.
 Submit the form to register a new user.
 Check the server console for registration success or error messages.


Contributing:-
 Feel free to contribute to the project. If you find any issues or have suggestions, please open an issue or submit a pull request.
